While researching cyberbullying, I realized that online behaviour can affect someone’s mental health much more than we think. Earlier I thought online comments are not very serious, but while studying this topic I understood how harmful repeated negative comments or trolling can be.
What surprised me most was that many victims do not report cyberbullying because they feel scared or embarrassed. I also learned that even small jokes online can hurt someone if they are repeated or said publicly.
After learning about this topic, one habit I want to change personally is being more careful about what I post or comment online. Even if something feels normal to me, it might hurt someone else. I also understood the importance of supporting someone if they are facing such problems instead of ignoring it.
This task made me more aware that being responsible online is not only about safety but also about respecting others. It changed my thinking about how important kindness is even in digital spaces.
